# Data Architecture

## Where each dataset lives

| Dataset | Storage | Seed source | Cache |
|---|---|---|---|
| Countries (205 entries) | `countries` SQL table | `countries_seed.py` | `data.COUNTRIES` set |
| Names (1455 Polish names) | `names` SQL table | `names_seed.py` | `data.NAMES` set |
| Jobs | `data.JOBS` set in `data.py` | *(legacy file-based)* | n/a |
| Rooms / players / scores | SQL tables in `db.py` | runtime | n/a |

**`JOBS` is still file-based on purpose.** The user said
*"narazie nie dotykaj zawodów"* — the PKD-derived job names are awkward
and need to be curated before migrating to SQL. Don't migrate
proactively.

## Seeding pattern (when adding a new dataset)

1. Generate a `*_seed.py` module with a `TypedDict` row schema and a
   `Final` list of seed entries.
2. Add `CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS ...` + `INSERT OR IGNORE` in
   `db.init_db()`.
3. Add `async def load_X_norms() -> set[str]` in `db.py`.
4. Add `async def reload_X()` in `data.py` that calls `load_X_norms()`
   and mutates the in-memory set in place.
5. Call `await reload_X()` from the FastAPI lifespan in `main.py`
   **after** `await init_db()`.
6. Call `asyncio.run(data.reload_X())` from `_isolated_test_db` in
   `tests/conftest.py`.

## Sonar exclusions

Seed modules and one-off scripts are excluded from Sonar analysis in
`sonar-project.properties`:

```
sonar.exclusions=\
  **/countries_seed.py,\
  **/names_seed.py,\
  scripts/**,\
  data/**,\
  ...
```

If you add a new `*_seed.py`, **add it to `sonar.exclusions`** —
otherwise Sonar will spam "Define a constant instead of duplicating
this literal" warnings on legitimate seed data.

## Database file

Single SQLite file `panstwa-miasta.db` in the repo root, gitignored.
Tests get isolated DBs via the `_isolated_test_db` fixture (each test
runs against a fresh temp file).
